<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871210-0077 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:Five Mars Stores DirectorsHave Resigned, Firm Says</HL><DD> 12/10/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MXXX WNEWS </IN><DATELINE> NORTH DIGHTON, Mass.  </DATELINE><TEXT>    Mars Stores Inc., a discountdepartment store chain that has reported sagging sales inrecent months, said five of its 10 directors resigned lastweek.   The company didn't identify the directors or indicate why they resigned and company officials couldn't be reached for comment last night to elaborate on the resignations.    In a news release issued after the stock market closed, Mars said: &quot;None of the directors who resigned expressed any disagreement with the company on any matter relating to the company's operations, policies or practices.&quot;    For the six months ended Aug. 1, Mars reported a loss of $1.4 million on sales of $45.1 million compared with a loss of $378,000 in the year-earlier period on sales of $47.2 million.    Mars shares closed yesterday at $1.50, off 12.5 cents, in national over-the-counter trading. </TEXT></DOC>